<item>
            <title>[JDK-8300266] Detect Virtualization on Linux aarch64</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8300266</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Currently we detect virtualization on Linux x86_64 (cpuid call) and Linux ppc64le ;  the result is afterwards used e.g. in hs_err and  JFR output.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
On Linux aarch64 the detection is missing, this should be added.&lt;br/&gt;
One option would be to look at /sys/devices/virtual/dmi/id/product_name and related files , at least KVM and VMWare can be detected quite well using these files.&lt;br/&gt;
Maybe other options exist.&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
